It has been shaped in metal clay, sanded and fired in a kiln. It was then oxidized, brushed and the flowers were sanded and polished to a high shine. The end result being a pure bronze pendant that is completely unique. A quality piece that will last a lifetime!
The brown silk necklace is finished with plated findings, it measures approx. 47cm long with an additional 6cm long extension chain.

This glass bead was handmade by me in my Sydney based studio. The last photo shows an example of the bead making process, winding molten glass onto a steel rod.

I make these using quality mirrors and each one has a layer of mylar plastic over the fabric to keep it clean. 
They measure 2 1/4 inches in diameter and come with an organza bag for gift giving.
